                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/362: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reber</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-29T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 29, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. Your 162, November 22, noon. Department has received request from the
                    Liberian Consul General<note n="46" xml:id="d344fn46">Not printed.</note> under
                    instructions from his Government for the Department to transmit the memorandum
                    which the Secretary of State delivered to him November 17. The following is the
                    text of the memorandum:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of the memorandum, printed on <ref target="#pg_369">page
                        369</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
